<tree expanded="true" show_heading="true" show_metadata="true" toc="false" root="false" taxon="Definition"><frontmatter> <anchor>118</anchor> <addr>def_simplicial_complex</addr> <sourcePath>/Users/bernardo/mega/Forest/trees/def_simplicial_complex.tree</sourcePath> <route>def_simplicial_complex.xml</route> <date>September 4, 2023</date> <authors><author><link href="bernardohummes.xml" type="local">Bernardo Hummes Flores</link></author> </authors> <title>Simplicial complex</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em>Simplicial complex</em> is a pair <tex>\mathcal{K} =(V,S)</tex>, where <tex>V</tex> is a finite set of vertices and <tex>S  \subseteq   \mathcal{P} (V)</tex> is a set of simplices, non-empty subsets of <tex>V</tex>, where:</p><p>+ For every <tex>v  \in  V, v  \in  S</tex></p><p>+ <tex>S</tex> is downards closed, i.e. for every <tex>Y  \in  S</tex> and for every non-empty subset <tex>X  \subseteq  Y, X  \in  S</tex>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related/> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>